statement.p:
Evaluate the function.
    f(x)=\begin{cases}
        4 \amp  x \lt 1\\
        5+2x-x^2  \amp  1\le x\lt 3\\
        2x \amp  x \gt 3
        \end{cases}

Sketch a graph of the function, and evaluate for the inputs below.
    g(x)=\begin{cases}
        x+2 \amp  x \lt -1\\
        1  \amp  -1\lt x\lt 1\\
        x \amp  x \ge 1
        \end{cases}

solution.p:
We apply the property of proportions and cross-multiply to get
    2.4x \amp = 1.5(8.4) \amp \amp \blert{\text{Divide both sides by 2.4.}}
        x \amp = \dfrac{1.5(8.4)}{2.4}  \amp \amp \blert{\text{Simplify the right side.}}
        x \amp = 5.25
